{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:philippians.2",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "philippians",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2",
    "summary": "Source text for Philippians 2 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:1",
      "text": "So if there is any encouragement in Christ, any incentive of love, any participation in the Spirit, any affection and sympathy,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:2",
      "text": "complete my joy by being of the same mind, having the same love, being in full accord and of one mind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:3",
      "text": "Do nothing from selfishness or conceit, but in humility count others better than yourselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:4",
      "text": "Let each of you look not only to his own interests, but also to the interests of others.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:5",
      "text": "Have this mind among yourselves, which is yours in Christ Jesus,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:6",
      "text": "who, though he was in the form of God, did not count equality with God a thing to be grasped,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:7",
      "text": "but emptied himself, taking the form of a servant, being born in the likeness of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:8",
      "text": "And being found in human form he humbled himself and became obedient unto death, even death on a cross.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:9",
      "text": "Therefore God has highly exalted him and bestowed on him the name which is above every name,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:10",
      "text": "that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, in heaven and on earth and under the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:11",
      "text": "and every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:12",
      "text": "Therefore, my beloved, as you have always obeyed, so now, not only as in my presence but much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:13",
      "text": "for God is at work in you, both to will and to work for his good pleasure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:14",
      "text": "Do all things without grumbling or questioning,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:15",
      "text": "that you may be blameless and innocent, children of God without blemish in the midst of a crooked and perverse generation, among whom you shine as lights in the world,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:16",
      "text": "holding fast the word of life, so that in the day of Christ I may be proud that I did not run in vain or labor in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:17",
      "text": "Even if I am to be poured as a libation upon the sacrificial offering of your faith, I am glad and rejoice with you all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:18",
      "text": "Likewise you also should be glad and rejoice with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:19",
      "text": "I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you soon, so that I may be cheered by news of you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:20",
      "text": "I have no one like him, who will be genuinely anxious for your welfare.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:21",
      "text": "They all look after their own interests, not those of Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:22",
      "text": "But Timothy's worth you know, how as a son with a father he has served with me in the gospel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:23",
      "text": "I hope therefore to send him just as soon as I see how it will go with me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:24",
      "text": "and I trust in the Lord that shortly I myself shall come also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:25",
      "text": "I have thought it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus my brother and fellow worker and fellow soldier, and your messenger and minister to my need,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:26",
      "text": "for he has been longing for you all, and has been distressed because you heard that he was ill.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:27",
      "text": "Indeed he was ill, near to death. But God had mercy on him, and not only on him but on me also, lest I should have sorrow upon sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:28",
      "text": "I am the more eager to send him, therefore, that you may rejoice at seeing him again, and that I may be less anxious.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:29",
      "text": "So receive him in the Lord with all joy; and honor such men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:philippians.2.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "philippians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Philippians 2:30",
      "text": "for he nearly died for the work of Christ, risking his life to complete your service to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
